thing that fits well into what I want. I want to ask you guys in case there’s something I’ve overlooked. Perhaps I’ll have to create this type of niche software myself? Wanted features:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Easily editable pages like a wiki, but also for non-technical people. WYSIWYG and not too many buttons&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Events with calendar. Again, easy to use&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus: Marketplace&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bonus: Simple stack. Just a binary/docker and an sqlite-file+assets would be great.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 23 Feb 2021 07:36:13 -0600</pubDate></item><item><title>Swift Ownership Manifesto</title><link>https://github.com/apple/swift/blob/main/docs/OwnershipManifesto.md</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/u5ekgp/swift_ownership_manifesto"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 23 Feb 2021 06:46:10 -0600</pubDate></item><item><title>Mental Models Box</title><link>https://www.mentalmodelsbox.com/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/oq6nmf/mental_models_box"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 23 Feb 2021 06:34:16 -0600</pubDate></item><item><title>Making our own executable packer</title><link>https://fasterthanli.me/series/making-our-own-executable-packer</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/sizbxs/making_our_own_executable_packer"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 23 Feb 2021 03:47:11 -0600</pubDate></item><item><title>Serve files securely on NetBSD over HTTPS via bozotic-httpd</title><link>https://www.unitedbsd.com/d/404-serve-files-securely-on-netbsd-over-https-via-bozotic-httpd</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/zaezpa/serve_files_securely_on_netbsd_over_https"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 23 Feb 2021 02:53:41 -0600</pubDate></item><item><title>systemE: A lightweight systemd replacement written in Emacs lisp</title><link>https://github.com/grandfoobah/systemE</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/gn5vbi/systeme_lightweight_systemd"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 22 Feb 2021 19:39:20 -0600</pubDate></item><item><title>Booting the IBM 1401: How a 1959 punch-card computer loads a program</title><link>http://www.righto.com/2021/02/an-ibm-1401-mainframe-computer-at.html</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/ytakzh/booting_ibm_1401_how_1959_punch_card"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 22 Feb 2021 22:07:30 -0600</pubDate></item><item><title>Integrating Rust and C++ in Firefox</title><link>http://manishearth.github.io/blog/2021/02/22/integrating-rust-and-c-plus-plus-in-firefox/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/wcjdny/integrating_rust_c_firefox"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 22 Feb 2021 16:56:04 -0600</pubDate></item><item><title>What are you doing this week?</title><link>https://lobste.rs/s/f4ytzp/what_are_you_doing_this_week</link><description>&lt;p&gt;What are you doing this week? Feel free to share!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Keep in mind it’s OK to do nothing at all, too.&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 22 Feb 2021 04:49:26 -0600</pubDate></item><item><title>Firefox 86 Introduces Total Cookie Protection</title><link>https://blog.mozilla.org/security/2021/02/23/total-cookie-protection/</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/rzuirb/firefox_86_introduces_total_cookie"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 23 Feb 2021 08:08:23 -0600</pubDate></item><item><title>Introducing veb(4) - a new Virtual Ethernet Bridge</title><link>http://undeadly.org/cgi?action=article;sid=20210223111210</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/p9aedd/introducing_veb_4_new_virtual_ethernet"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 23 Feb 2021 08:07:02 -0600</pubDate></item><item><title>Dropbox-like (selective sync) OSS file synchronization for home</title><link>https://lobste.rs/s/vf3wez/dropbox_like_selective_sync_oss_file</link><description>&lt;p&gt;Hi, I really like how it is possible with Dropbox to have some files present locally and some only remotely.
Is there a similar open source solution? It could be a product but I would prefer an open source and something I can personally run at home.&lt;br&gt;
E.g I want to have my notes/keepass to be always present on my Android phone and desktop to allow offline access. The rest of the files could be remote only.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;My current solution is to have a SMB share and use Syncthing to sync a certain directory (e.g Notes). But combining multiple solutions feels a bit hacky so I am looking for alternatives.&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 23 Feb 2021 04:10:16 -0600</pubDate></item><item><title>Can we contain mutable data in imperative languages?</title><link>https://leontrolski.github.io/alter.html</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/qstow5/can_we_contain_mutable_data_imperative"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Mon, 22 Feb 2021 11:23:33 -0600</pubDate></item><item><title>Time for Next-Gen Codecs to Dethrone JPEG</title><link>https://cloudinary.com/blog/time_for_next_gen_codecs_to_dethrone_jpeg</link><description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="https://lobste.rs/s/vekkco/time_for_next_gen_codecs_dethrone_jpeg"&gt;Comments&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><pubDate>Tue, 23 Feb 2021 05:56:35 -0600</pubDate></item></channel></rss>